.\" termin.al-name: man
.\" termin.al-usage: man [-P less|vi] [--pager=less|vi] <command>
.\" termin.al-summary: Show a command manual.
.TH MAN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
man \- Show a command manual.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
man <command>
man -P less|vi <command>
man --pager=less|vi <command>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reads a project-authored section-1 manual for a registered command. The default and less presentations open the generated text in the raw pager. The vi presentation opens the same text with a highlighted current line and NORMAL status.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "-P " "less|vi"
Select the less or vi manpager presentation.
.TP
.BI "--pager=" "less|vi"
Select the less or vi manpager presentation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ man grep
$ man -P less grep
$ man --pager=vi pane
.fi
.SH NOTES
Manual sources are roff files generated to checked UTF-8 artifacts during the production build. All presentations use the same artifact. Aliases resolve through the command registry to the canonical manual. Use q or Escape to close either pager; Ctrl+b remains the pane-prefix key.
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), less(1)
